aining much evil. The book is at once analytic in style and Hasidic in broad orientation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aGod (Judaism) 0aGod (Judaism). 0aOrthodox JudaismxDoctrines. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Theology.2bisacsh  aCritique of post-modernism.  aGod.  aHasidic Judaism.  aHasidic thought.  aHasidism.  aJewish theology.  aJudaism.  aOld Testament.  aapologetics.  abelief.  aepistemology.  aevil.  ahumility response.  amodern religious life.  amorality.  aperfect goodness.  aphilosophy.  apossible theodicy.  areligious philosophy.  atheology.  atruth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311068819108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertReligious Studies ASPz978311071683240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644691373zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644691373423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644691373/original  a978-3-11-068819-1  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-071683-2  Religious Studies ASP  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK